<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-12T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="875" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d875">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/16</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-12T11:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s January 11, midnight. Am in Juarez conferring with General
                            Gavira and Consul Garcia. They are endeavoring to comply with
                            Department’s request transmitted by me. General Gavira states he has
                            already sent troops out on Northwestern road from Juarez and that he has
                            been informed by General Treviño that troops have already been sent west
                            from Chihuahua over that division of Northwestern.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>